Cyclone Burevi is likely to hit the Thiruvananthapuram coast by Friday noon.
Heavy rains have been predicted in Thiruvananthapuram, Kollam, Pathanamthitta, Alappuzha,
Kottayam, Idukki and Ernakulam. Reports are that heavy rains will continue from December 3 to 5
in these districts. People in Thiruvananthapuram can reach the district administration in case
of emergency situations by calling the control room number 1077. Stay with TOI for all the
latest updates: